rComments: Elle donne du bon feedback après les présentations. On ne la voit pas souvent, mais elle semble gentille.
I really liked to improve my communication skills but it was very tough for a summer course. I was expecting to get a better grade.

Prof Gagnon has an unflappably positive attitude and always has a smile on her face. She made the class interesting with videos and short films. She did reviews before each midterm and the exam of exactly what you had to study. She always stayed after class to answer questions and clarify. Definitely the French Comm. Org. prof to have in 1st year!

(French immersion student) Loved her. Very nice and lectures were interesting. She spoke clearly, not too fast and wears a mic so everyone can hear. She posts her lectures online so attendance isn't necessary. She has participation marks (that are easy) so I recommend going. Exams are easy as long as you listen!

Absolutely loved the prof and the class. She's pretty awesome. Her ''midterms'' are super easy, they're basically copy and paste from her slides and maybe one or two from the readings you had to do. I would definitely take again this class or any other class that she teaches.

Nicest and sweetest teacher. She is there to help, and will generally end class half an hour early to answer questions from students. Consists of three midterms and the final, all being multiple choice for a total of 150 questions all year. Would take a class just because she is the prof.
Diane is a wonderful prof! She's always there to answer any questions. Go to class, take notes and you will do great! I definitely recommend taking a class with her.
Love the class! She's super clear in her explications and she gives really good examples of every day life during her lectures!

The best prof I have ever had. Lectures were clear, midterms and quizzes were really easy. The final was more difficult but I still got an A. Really nice woman. I would love to take a class with her again.

Extremely nice & fair prof, with conversational style. Apart from some tricky multiple choice on the only exam, her assignments are graded fairly & you'd have to really not be trying to fail her class. Participant is important as she randomly asks questions that are marked throughout the semester. Assignments have small % weight & are plentiful.

A new professor. I had her last semester. She's very sweet and approachable. You can tell she caring and passionate. Her lectures are interesting. It was a long class but I actually enjoyed attending it.
